<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 06 at 1:18PM MDT until July 06 at 2:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 200 PM MDT
FOR NORTHEASTERN JUDITH BASIN AND WEST CENTRAL FERGUS COUNTIES...
At 118 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Stanford,
moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Stanford, Denton, Coffee Creek, Windham and Benchland.
TORNADO...POSSIBLE
HAIL THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>This storm is producing large hail. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows.</instruction>
